Review mode: static diff review of `git diff 61f7386..HEAD` plus targeted file inspection.

## Verdict: CONCERN

### 1. [medium] Panic-class parity is only enforced on the async engine paths, not every `#[napi]` entry point

Refs:

- [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-napi/src/lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-11b-napi-binding-20260516T210327Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-napi/src/lib.rs:16)
- [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-napi/src/lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-11b-napi-binding-20260516T210327Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-napi/src/lib.rs:268)
- [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-napi/src/lib.rs](/tmp/fdb-11b-napi-binding-20260516T210327Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-napi/src/lib.rs:432)

The module-level contract says every `#[napi]` entry point catches Rust panics and rethrows the documented `FDB_PANIC` / `FathomDbPanicError` class. That is true for the async engine calls routed through `call_engine()` and for `Engine.open()`, but the synchronous exported methods `counters()`, `set_profiling()`, `set_slow_threshold_ms()`, and `attach_subscriber()` are plain `#[napi]` methods with no explicit `catch_unwind` wrapper.

That means a panic escaping one of those entry points would fall back to napi-rs's default panic conversion instead of the documented typed panic path. This is a contract gap rather than a demonstrated happy-path failure, but it means the Phase 11b panic guarantee is not uniformly enforced at the FFI boundary.

### 2. [low] AC-057a is not cited in the TypeScript surface tests

Refs:

- [src/ts/tests/surface.test.ts](/tmp/fdb-11b-napi-binding-20260516T210327Z/src/ts/tests/surface.test.ts:1)
- [src/ts/tests/ffi-safety.test.ts](/tmp/fdb-11b-napi-binding-20260516T210327Z/src/ts/tests/ffi-safety.test.ts:1)
- [src/ts/tests/typed-errors.test.ts](/tmp/fdb-11b-napi-binding-20260516T210327Z/src/ts/tests/typed-errors.test.ts:1)
- [src/ts/tests/save-time-validation.test.ts](/tmp/fdb-11b-napi-binding-20260516T210327Z/src/ts/tests/save-time-validation.test.ts:1)
- [src/ts/tests/no-recovery-surface.test.ts](/tmp/fdb-11b-napi-binding-20260516T210327Z/src/ts/tests/no-recovery-surface.test.ts:1)

The prompt asked for acceptance-ID traceability covering `AC-057a`, `AC-060a`, `AC-060b`, `AC-067`, `AC-068a`, `AC-068b`, and `AC-041`. The suite cites all of the latter IDs, but `surface.test.ts` does not cite `AC-057a` the way the 11a Python PASS remediation did. The five-verb surface itself looks preserved; this is a traceability miss in the test annotation layer.

## Notes

- `fathomdb-napi` is present as a workspace member in [Cargo.toml](/tmp/fdb-11b-napi-binding-20260516T210327Z/Cargo.toml:1), and the crate manifest sets `publish = false` in [src/rust/crates/fathomdb-napi/Cargo.toml](/tmp/fdb-11b-napi-binding-20260516T210327Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-napi/Cargo.toml:1).
